<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 11 at 9:51PM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...Brief Heavy Snow Showers...
Scattered to numerous snow showers will move across the region
through the rest of the evening. Some of the snow showers will
produce a rapid drop in visibility below a mile at times and leave
quick coating on the roads. The duration of the heaviest snow
should not be more than a half hour in any given location. Drivers
should be prepared for rapidly fluctuating visibilities and slick
roads.</description>
